# Move Me To EU — Project Rules & Context

This file exists so any Claude session can jump into this project without re-deriving decisions, rediscovering gotchas, or repeating conversations. Treat it as the authoritative source of project context. Update it when decisions change.

---

## Project identity

**Product:** Move Me To EU — a React/Vite single-page tool that matches users to EU countries based on visa pathway eligibility, priority weightings, and side-by-side comparisons across 27 EU member states. Sibling product to mywiserelocation.com / mywisetravel.com.

**Live URL:** https://movemeto.eu
**Temporary URL:** https://movemeto-eu.onrender.com (disable once apex is live)
**GitHub:** https://github.com/jfsubs/movemeto-eu
**Owner:** Justin (jfsubs on GitHub), dual US/German citizen, Arlington VA, planning family relocation to Germany (Aachen top candidate)

**Product philosophy:** Honest data over marketing claims. Every figure shown is researched from official sources with a "verify at the portal before acting" disclaimer. The tool is not legal advice; it's a first-cut sorting mechanism for people who don't know where to start.

