## SEO and metadata baseline (April 28 2026)

The site is indexable by default. A full SEO baseline is in place; don't add `<meta name="robots" content="noindex">`.

What's deployed:

- **`index.html`** — title, meta description (under 160 chars), canonical (`https://movemeto.eu/`), full Open Graph + Twitter Card metadata, two JSON-LD blocks (`WebApplication` + `FAQPage`), preconnects to Google Fonts and the Twemoji CDN
- **`public/robots.txt`** — allow-all, points to sitemap, defensive `Disallow: /*onrender.com*` rule
- **`public/sitemap.xml`** — single URL (`/`) since the SPA has no per-route URLs
- **`public/og-image.png`** — 1200×630, EU blue + gold, regeneratable from `public/og-image.svg` (in-repo source). The PNG was rendered with TeX Gyre Bonum + Liberation Sans as Fraunces/Manrope substitutes in a sandboxed environment; for pixel-perfect brand fidelity, re-render the SVG locally with the actual brand fonts installed (`magick og-image.svg og-image.png` works once Fraunces and Manrope are on the rendering machine)

Cross-cutting things to keep in sync:

- **WebApplication JSON-LD** describes the tool — `featureList`, `about`, audience, the 9 visa types listed by name. If the visa type list in `MoveMeToEU.jsx` changes, update the `about` array
- **FAQPage JSON-LD** mirrors `FAQ_ITEMS` from `MoveMeToEU.jsx`. See "FAQ view" decision above for sync rules
- **OG image dimensions** — 1200×630 is the de facto standard. Don't change without updating both meta tags (`og:image:width`, `og:image:height`) and verifying preview behavior across LinkedIn / iMessage / Slack / X
- **Canonical URL** — points at the apex (`https://movemeto.eu/`). The Render preview subdomain is disabled (April 28 2026) so duplicate-content risk is contained; if it's ever re-enabled, that subdomain needs `noindex` and a canonical pointing back at apex (see "What NOT to do" below)

What's deliberately *not* in place:

- A separate content site at the apex. The `mywiserelocation.com` domain is being developed as a separate content/blog property that links *into* `movemeto.eu` — not a redirect, not a mirror. The two domains target different SEO surfaces (`movemeto.eu` for tool-shaped queries, `mywiserelocation.com` for educational long-form content). Don't propose merging them or redirecting one to the other
- Per-page URLs for individual countries / visa types. Adding routes was rejected (see "What NOT to do" #6). The SEO consequence is real but accepted — the FAQ schema and tool-shaped queries are the chosen ranking surface

When SEO content changes (FAQ, OG image, structured data), validate before deploying:

- JSON-LD blocks parse cleanly. Quick check from the repo root:
  ```bash
  python3 -c "import json,re; html=open('index.html').read(); [json.loads(b) for b in re.findall(r'<script type=\"application/ld\+json\">(.*?)</script>', html, re.DOTALL)]; print('OK')"
  ```
- Open Graph preview: paste the URL into [opengraph.xyz](https://www.opengraph.xyz/) or directly into Slack / iMessage as a sanity check
- Rich Results Test: [search.google.com/test/rich-results](https://search.google.com/test/rich-results) confirms Google sees both schemas

