## What NOT to do

Decisions that have been tried and rejected, or suggestions that waste time:

1. **Don't introduce a UI framework.** The app is deliberately framework-free. Adding Tailwind/MUI/Chakra would require a full restyle for zero user benefit.
2. **Don't use Unicode flag emoji.** Use `<Flag code="XX" />`. The emoji fails on Windows browsers.
3. **Don't suggest ALIAS records at Joker.** A records are the decided path.
4. **Don't flat-average the match score.** The non-linear + bonus/penalty algorithm is deliberate.
5. **Don't use emoji in the tool outside of flags.** Icons for visas (◆ ● ◇ ◈ ♥ ✦ ◎ ☼ ★) are Unicode geometric symbols, not emoji — they render consistently everywhere.
6. **Don't create separate page routes.** Everything is a view toggle inside the single-page app. Adding React Router would require Render rewrite rules and complicate deployment for no benefit.
7. **Don't add tier labels to cross-border data** (Low/Moderate/High on homicide, etc.). Peer-relative tiers mislead across borders.
8. **Don't include localStorage/sessionStorage.** Not needed; state is intentionally per-session.
9. **Don't scaffold npm scripts for production tests** (Jest, Vitest, etc.). If adding tests becomes needed, ask first — the project deliberately ships without a test harness to keep the iteration loop fast.
10. **Don't propose dark mode.** Not in scope.
11. **Don't remove the Step 2 priority budget cap.** Free 0–5 sliders for all 13 factors collapse the scoring algorithm because everyone sets everything to 5. The friction is the feature.
12. **Don't reintroduce dealbreaker thresholds.** Removed April 2026 — replaced by the implicit weighted-5 penalty. See "Dealbreaker thresholds: removed" decision above.
13. **Don't widen `PRIORITY_BONUS_POOL` past 5 casually.** The bonus/penalty thresholds in the scoring algorithm are tuned for the spread of weight distributions users actually produce under a 5-point budget. Changing the pool requires re-tuning.
14. **Don't bypass the intro fork.** "Find your match" routes to the entry-mode picker (`entryMode === null`), not directly to wizard Step 0. Top-nav "Pathway Finder" and Why EU's "Find your match →" CTA both reset `entryMode` to `null` for this reason.
15. **Don't add weight bumps to branched quiz questions.** The +5 priority budget is spent exactly by the 5 universal value trade-offs. Branched eligibility questions populate `profile` and (sometimes) `selectedVisa`, never `weights`. Adding bumps breaks the 100%-used budget invariant on Step 3.
16. **Don't ship `.webp` files that are actually JPGs.** Always run an actual conversion pass (Squoosh or `magick`). Renaming `.jpg` to `.webp` works in browsers but balloons file size by 20–50× and defeats the point of WebP.
17. **Don't auto-rotate the hero without honoring `prefers-reduced-motion`.** The current implementation disables the interval entirely when the media query matches. Don't replace this with a "slow rotation" — reduced-motion users want no motion, not less motion.
18. **Don't use Unicode emoji in the hero or as visual UI flourish.** The intro-fork card icons (`◇` / `◆`) are Unicode geometric symbols, same convention as visa icons. Emoji break on Windows browsers and add an inconsistent vendor-styling layer.
19. **Don't add `<meta name="robots" content="noindex">` to `index.html`.** The site went indexable on April 28 2026 with a full SEO baseline (canonical, OG, JSON-LD, sitemap). If a specific future content needs hiding, use a `Disallow` rule in `robots.txt` on the relevant path; don't block the apex.
20. **Don't let `FAQ_ITEMS` and the `FAQPage` JSON-LD diverge.** They mirror each other intentionally. Compressed answer text in JSON-LD is fine; a question or substantive fact appearing in one but not the other is not.
21. **Don't re-enable the `movemeto-eu.onrender.com` preview subdomain** without first adding `<meta name="robots" content="noindex">` to its served HTML and a canonical pointing to the apex. Two domains serving identical content is the primary SEO risk for this project — the previous duplicate-content situation was the reason the preview was disabled in the first place.
22. **Don't redirect or mirror `mywiserelocation.com` to `movemeto.eu`.** The two domains are intentionally a separate-properties pair: `movemeto.eu` is the tool, `mywiserelocation.com` is the content/blog site that links into it. They target different SEO surfaces. Merging them collapses both into a worse version of one.
23. **Don't use em-dashes in user-facing prose Claude authors for this project.** This is a standing voice preference. Replace with commas, semicolons, colons, or split into separate sentences. The rule applies to bio paragraphs, service descriptions, FAQ answers, in-app copy, marketing copy, and any other prose that ships to users. It does not apply to internal documentation (this file, code comments, commit messages), to em-dashes that already exist in Justin's data tables or country-specific visa entries (leave those alone unless Justin asks for a sweep), or to chat responses Claude writes back to Justin (those follow normal conventions). The rule is about what users read, not what Justin and Claude exchange while building.
24. **Don't gate prices behind contact forms on the services page.** Transparency was researched and is the deliberate competitive position. "Contact for pricing," "request a quote," and similar patterns are exactly what the page is positioned against. See "Advisory services pricing philosophy."
25. **Don't propose a subscription or membership tier on the services page.** Rejected at launch. Don't re-propose without 30+ past clients and an obvious community-surface demand signal. See "Advisory services pricing philosophy."
26. **Don't propose competing with Tier 2 destination services on in-country settling-in work** (apartment hunting, Anmeldung accompaniment, school registration, lease checks). These require physical presence in Germany; Justin's own move is years out. Refer these out, don't build them. See "Advisory services pricing philosophy."
27. **Don't re-add the asylum case or the high-speed rail article to the bio.** Both were drafted into earlier versions of the About me section and removed in Justin's May 2026 edit pass. Don't re-propose without explicit instruction. See "Bio voice and content rules" for the full list of excluded elements.
28. **Don't name FMP / Federal Management Partners or specific federal clients (NGA, NSF, etc.) in the bio.** Justin's day job is described as "a professional services firm in Arlington, Virginia" by deliberate choice. Don't refactor this back to specifics. See "Bio voice and content rules."
29. **Don't claim PMP certification or a specific German language proficiency level for Justin.** PMP is in progress, not earned. German level is not publicly stated. Don't fabricate either.

